<paragraph blockId="3.[151,760,385,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,298,385,408]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Distribution.</emphasis>
This is the first record of this species from both the 
<collectingCountry box="[251,425,417,440]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[442,542,417,440]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Bohemia</collectingCountry>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[608,705,417,440]" name="Slovakia" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
. The species has hitherto been known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[611,695,449,472]" name="Finland" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Finland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Sweden" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Sweden</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[201,300,481,504]" name="Germany" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[308,381,481,504]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Russia</collectingCountry>
, and the Nearctic Region (
<bibRefCitation author="VILKAMAA P. &amp; HIPPA H." pageId="3" pageNumber="532" pagination="53 - 68" refId="ref4670" refString="VILKAMAA P. &amp; HIPPA H. 2007: Review of the Nearctic Claustropyga Hippa, Vilkamaa &amp; Mohrig (Diptera, Sciaridae) with the description of three new species. Zootaxa 1552: 53 - 68." type="journal article" year="2007">VILKAMAA &amp; HIPPA 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
